Deputy National Security Advisor for International Economics, Daleep Singh, will be visiting New Delhi on March 30th and 31st to continue discussions with the Government of India. The purpose of the visit is to address various issues related to the U.S.-India economic relationship and strategic partnership. Singh will meet with Indian officials to strengthen cooperation for inclusive economic growth, prosperity, and a free and open Indo-Pacific. Additionally, Singh will discuss the consequences of Russia's war against Ukraine and how to mitigate its impact on the global economy. The priorities of the Biden Administration, such as the promotion of high-quality infrastructure through the Build Back Better World initiative and the development of an Indo-Pacific Economic Framework, will also be discussed.